The Edo State Independent Electoral Commission (EDSIEC) has suspended the local government elections scheduled for April 19, 2022. According to a statement by Emmanuel Abebe on behalf of the Chairman of EDSIEC, the suspension of the exercise was due to the restraining order by the Federal High Court, Abuja on the Edo State Independent Electoral Commission.   Enugu 2023: Unspoken interests driving zoning commotion     Who will beat Ayade in 2023 governorship race?     Send your details, Tonto Dikeh replies Ada Karl over alleged…   The commission said all processes leading to the conduct of the elections have been suspended, pending the hearing and determination of the Motion on Notice. He said: “It is hereby announced for the information of the general public that due to the content of the publication in the Vanguard Newspaper of 7th April, 2022 by which the Federal High Court Abuja restrained the Edo State Independent Electoral Commission from conducting the Local Government Elections in the State scheduled for 19th April 2022, all processes leading to the conduct of the said elections are hereby suspended, pending the hearing and determination of the Motion on Notice.”